<div class="sa-faq-wrap" data-testid="sa-faq-wrap">
  <h1 class="sa-faq-title"><i class="bi bi-question-circle-fill"></i> SuperAdmin Help &amp; FAQ</h1>
  <p class="sa-faq-subtitle">
    Comprehensive operator guide for managing the platform —
    including the embedded ACE / TR-069 (GenieACS) console for ONT/ONU
    provisioning, firmware management and remote diagnostics.
  </p>

  <div class="sa-faq-toc">
    <h4>On this page</h4>
    <ol>
      <li><a href="#genieacs">GenieACS (ACE/TR-069) — Full Setup &amp; Usage Guide</a></li>
      <li><a href="#login-credentials">Login URL &amp; credentials</a></li>
      <li><a href="#first-time-setup">First-time setup walkthrough</a></li>
      <li><a href="#provision-onu">How to provision a new ONU/ONT</a></li>
      <li><a href="#daily-tasks">Day-to-day operator tasks</a></li>
      <li><a href="#troubleshooting">Troubleshooting &amp; common errors</a></li>
      <li><a href="#api-tokens">API tokens &amp; scripting</a></li>
      <li><a href="#security">Security recommendations</a></li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="sa-faq-card" id="genieacs">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-broadcast-pin"></i> GenieACS Setup &amp; Usage Guide <span class="badge">SuperAdmin only</span></h2>
    <p>
      GenieACS is the embedded TR-069 (ACS — Auto Configuration Server) inside
      this platform. It is responsible for provisioning, monitoring and
      remotely managing every ONT/ONU and CPE (router) that supports the
      CWMP protocol. The platform talks to GenieACS through an internal
      reverse proxy, so you should NEVER expose the GenieACS ports
      (7547 / 7557 / 7567) to the public internet directly.
    </p>
    <div class="sa-faq-callout">
      <strong>Where it runs:</strong> GenieACS runs as a systemd service on
      the same VPS as the billing portal. Status:
      <code>systemctl status genieacs-{cwmp,fs,ui,nbi}</code>.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sa-faq-card" id="login-credentials">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-key-fill"></i> Login URL &amp; Credentials</h2>
    <p>Use the credentials below to access the GenieACS web UI. These are
       the platform's <strong>default operator credentials</strong> — change
       them immediately on first login (see Security section).</p>
    <div class="sa-faq-creds">
      <div class="row"><span class="lbl">URL:</span>
        <code>https://acs.autoispbilling.com</code>
      </div>
      <div class="row"><span class="lbl">Username:</span>
        <code>admin</code>
      </div>
      <div class="row"><span class="lbl">Password:</span>
        <code>Acs@AdminPass2026</code>
      </div>
      <div class="row"><span class="lbl">CWMP URL:</span>
        <code>https://acs.autoispbilling.com:7547/</code>
      </div>
      <div class="row"><span class="lbl">NBI URL:</span>
        <code>http://127.0.0.1:7557/</code> <em style="color:#FBBF24;">(internal only)</em>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sa-faq-warning">
      <strong>Important:</strong> Treat these credentials as production-sensitive.
      Do NOT share them with Admins, Sub-LCOs or Employees. This help page is
      visible to SuperAdmins only. Anyone with the GenieACS password can
      remotely reconfigure every connected ONT/ONU on the network.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sa-faq-card" id="first-time-setup">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-rocket-takeoff-fill"></i> First-Time Setup Walkthrough</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Open the GenieACS UI</strong> at <a href="https://acs.autoispbilling.com" target="_blank">https://acs.autoispbilling.com</a>
          and sign in with the credentials above.</li>
      <li><strong>Change the default password</strong> immediately via
          <em>Admin → Users → admin → Change Password</em>. Save the new
          password in your password manager.</li>
      <li><strong>Verify the CWMP listener</strong> is reachable from your
          ONUs by SSH-ing into the VPS and running:
          <pre class="sa-faq-cmd">curl -I https://acs.autoispbilling.com:7547/</pre>
          You should see <code>HTTP/1.1 405 Method Not Allowed</code> — this
          is correct (the endpoint only accepts CWMP POSTs).</li>
      <li><strong>Confirm the four GenieACS services are running</strong>:
          <pre class="sa-faq-cmd">systemctl status genieacs-cwmp genieacs-fs genieacs-ui genieacs-nbi
# All four must show: Active: active (running)</pre></li>
      <li><strong>Set the ACS URL on every ONU/ONT</strong> from its own
          web interface or via your OLT's bulk-provision tool:
          <code>https://acs.autoispbilling.com:7547/</code>.
          Most TP-Link / V-SOL / D-Link units expose this under
          <em>Management → TR-069 → ACS URL</em>.</li>
      <li><strong>Trigger an Inform</strong> on the ONU. It should show up
          in GenieACS UI → Devices within 60 seconds.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="sa-faq-card" id="provision-onu">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-wifi"></i> Provisioning a New ONU/ONT</h2>
    <p>This is the recommended workflow for every new subscriber's CPE.</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Add the customer in the Admin Portal (Subscribers → Add). Note
          their Subscriber ID and assigned plan.</li>
      <li>Open the GenieACS UI and search for the ONU by serial number
          or MAC address.</li>
      <li>Click into the device's detail page. Under <em>Parameters</em>,
          locate <code>InternetGatewayDevice.WANDevice.1.WANConnectionDevice.1.WANPPPConnection.1</code>
          (or <code>WANIPConnection.1</code> for IPoE links).</li>
      <li>Set the credentials:
          <ul>
            <li><code>Username</code> = subscriber's RADIUS username</li>
            <li><code>Password</code> = subscriber's RADIUS password</li>
            <li><code>Enable</code> = true</li>
          </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Apply changes. GenieACS will push the configuration on the next
          Inform (typically within 30 seconds).</li>
      <li>Verify in the Admin Portal &gt; Online Users — the new subscriber
          should appear with their assigned IP.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="sa-faq-callout">
      <strong>Tip:</strong> Provisioning scripts can be saved as
      <em>Presets</em> in GenieACS UI → Admin → Presets, so the next time
      an ONU of the same vendor connects, settings auto-apply.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sa-faq-card" id="daily-tasks">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-calendar-check-fill"></i> Day-to-Day Operator Tasks</h2>
    <h3>Reboot a customer's ONU remotely</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Find the device in GenieACS UI.</li>
      <li>Open Actions → <em>Reboot</em>. The device should disconnect for
          30-60 seconds and re-Inform.</li>
    </ol>
    <h3>Push new Wi-Fi SSID / password to a router</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Open the device detail page.</li>
      <li>Edit <code>InternetGatewayDevice.LANDevice.1.WLANConfiguration.1.SSID</code>
          and <code>.PreSharedKey.1.KeyPassphrase</code>.</li>
      <li>Apply &amp; reboot the unit (some firmwares need a reboot).</li>
    </ol>
    <h3>Bulk firmware upgrade</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Upload the firmware file to GenieACS UI → Admin → Files.</li>
      <li>Create a Preset that targets the vendor/model and assigns the file
          to <code>DownloadDiagnosticState</code>.</li>
      <li>Apply the preset to the relevant device group.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="sa-faq-card" id="troubleshooting">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-tools"></i> Troubleshooting &amp; Common Errors</h2>
    <h3>ONU doesn't appear in GenieACS</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Verify the ACS URL on the ONU matches the CWMP listener exactly,
          including the trailing slash.</li>
      <li>Check the firewall: TCP 7547 inbound must be open from your
          subscriber network.</li>
      <li>Reboot the ONU and watch <code>journalctl -fu genieacs-cwmp</code>
          for the Inform request.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Inform received but parameters not pushed</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Open the device → <em>Tasks</em> queue and look for failed tasks.</li>
      <li>Check the ONU's CWMP credentials in
          <code>ManagementServer.Username</code> /
          <code>.Password</code>. They must match what your GenieACS
          security-realm expects.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Services not starting after reboot</h3>
    <pre class="sa-faq-cmd">sudo systemctl restart genieacs-cwmp genieacs-fs genieacs-ui genieacs-nbi
journalctl -u genieacs-cwmp -n 100 --no-pager</pre>
  </div>

  <div class="sa-faq-card" id="api-tokens">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-code-slash"></i> API Tokens &amp; Scripting</h2>
    <p>
      The billing portal uses a server-side token to call the GenieACS NBI
      (Northbound Interface). It is stored in:
    </p>
    <pre class="sa-faq-cmd">/opt/ispbilling/.acs_token  (chmod 600, owner: ispbilling)</pre>
    <p>
      Rotate it by generating a new token via:
    </p>
    <pre class="sa-faq-cmd">curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:7557/admin/tokens \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     -d '{"label":"billing-portal-2026"}'</pre>
    <p>Write the returned value into <code>/opt/ispbilling/.acs_token</code>
       and restart <code>isp-admin</code>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="sa-faq-card" id="security">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-shield-lock-fill"></i> Security Recommendations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Never expose the GenieACS UI publicly.</strong> Restrict
          access via Nginx <code>allow</code>/<code>deny</code> rules to
          your office IP range only.</li>
      <li><strong>Rotate the admin password every 90 days.</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Disable the default operator account</strong> once you
          have created a per-staff account (Admin → Users).</li>
      <li><strong>Enable TLS</strong> on port 7547 — the platform installer
          already terminates TLS at Nginx using the same Let's Encrypt
          cert as <code>autoispbilling.com</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Audit changes.</strong> GenieACS logs every push under
          <code>/var/log/genieacs-cwmp.log</code>. Review weekly.</li>
      <li><strong>This help page is restricted to SuperAdmins.</strong>
          Admins, Sub-LCOs and Employees CANNOT reach
          <code>/superadmin/faq</code> — the route is server-side gated
          by <code>require_superadmin()</code>.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="sa-faq-card">
    <h2><i class="bi bi-life-preserver"></i> Need more help?</h2>
    <p>
      If you encounter a scenario not covered above, raise a ticket via
      <a href="/superadmin/support">SuperAdmin → Support</a> or check the
      official GenieACS docs at
      <a href="https://github.com/genieacs/genieacs/wiki" target="_blank">https://github.com/genieacs/genieacs/wiki</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
